    {
      "Text": "Security update for the Linux Kernel (Live Patch 23 for SLE 12)",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "Summary"
    },
    {
      "Text": "This update for the Linux Kernel 3.12.61-52_80 fixes one issue.\n\nThe following security issues were fixed:\n\n- CVE-2017-15868: The bnep_add_connection function in net/bluetooth/bnep/core.c did not ensure that an l2cap socket is available, which allowed local users to gain privileges via a crafted application (bsc#1071471).\n",
      "Title": "Details",
      "Type": "General"
    },
